chunks.text:

When the relationship dissolved;

The reason for the dissolution of the relationship;


The temporal relationship between the ending of the relationship and the forming of a
new relationship with the subsequent partner;

Evidence that the former spouses or partners did not separate or end contact with each
other;

the intent of the spouses or partners upon re-establishing their relationship;

the length of the subsequent relationship;

the temporal connection between the dissolving of the subsequent relationship and the
re-establishment of a new relationship with the previous spouse or partner, and;

the intentions of the parties to the new relationship with respect to immigration.

